<body>

   

    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>Delicious & Healthy Pongal Recipe</h1>
        

        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>1 cup Raw Rice</li>
            <li>1/2 cup Moong Dal (Yellow Lentils)</li>
            <li>4 cups Water</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp Turmeric Powder</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Ghee</li>
            <li>1 tsp Black Pepper (coarsely crushed)</li>
            <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
            <li>10 Cashew Nuts</li>
            <li>1-inch Ginger (finely chopped)</li>
            <li>A few Curry Leaves</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Dry roast moong dal until slightly golden and fragrant.</li>
            <li>In a pressure cooker, add rice, roasted dal, turmeric, salt, and water.</li>
            <li>Cook for 3-4 whistles until soft and mushy.</li>
            <li>In a pan, heat ghee and fry cashews until golden.</li>
            <li>Add black pepper, cumin seeds, chopped ginger, and curry leaves.</li>
            <li>Pour this tempering over the cooked Pongal and mix well.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
